cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SY

The paper deals with resource allocation and network coding techniques for multimedia multicast services, which are typically studied in the networking and communication fields. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also focuses on multimedia services, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of packet error probability expressions and optimization frameworks indicates that it could also be classified under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper aims to offer service guarantees to a predetermined fraction of users, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
